Sentencas: Metallic materials, especially Fe-Cr ferritic alloys, are promising as interconnect materials of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) operated at around medium temperatures.
Titulo: Effect of Mn-Co spinel coating for Fe-Cr ferritic alloys ZMG232L and 232J3 for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects on oxidation behavior and Cr-evaporation

Sentencas: ZMG232L is one of the developed Fe-Cr ferritic alloys for SOFC metallic interconnects.
Titulo: Effect of Mn-Co spinel coating for Fe-Cr ferritic alloys ZMG232L and 232J3 for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects on oxidation behavior and Cr-evaporation

Sentencas: These metallic materials are usually machined or pressed into various shapes of interconnect parts, and thickness of these parts is often thin.
Titulo: Effect of Mn-Co spinel coating for Fe-Cr ferritic alloys ZMG232L and 232J3 for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects on oxidation behavior and Cr-evaporation

Sentencas: However, the oxidation rate of thin sheet was much higher than that of thick one because Cr content decreased under oxide layer of edge part of thin sheet.
Titulo: Effect of Mn-Co spinel coating for Fe-Cr ferritic alloys ZMG232L and 232J3 for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects on oxidation behavior and Cr-evaporation

Sentencas: Such accelerated oxidation behavior could be improved by reducing Mn, increasing Cr, and adding Win ZMG232L.
Titulo: Effect of Mn-Co spinel coating for Fe-Cr ferritic alloys ZMG232L and 232J3 for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects on oxidation behavior and Cr-evaporation

Sentencas: It is also very important to reduce Cr-evaporation from the oxidized surface of ferritic alloys in cathode side.

Sentencas: The aim of this study is to reduce the Cr-evaporation from oxidized alloy surface in air by coating with Mn-Co spinel oxide.
